EXECUTIVE CHAMBERS
KE KE'ENA O KE KIA'.A.INA
JOSH GREEN, M.D.
GOVERNOR
KE KIA'AINA
April 23, 2026
The Honorable Ronald D. Kouchi The Honorable Nadine K. Nakamura
President of the Senate Speaker of the House of Representatives
Thirty-Third State Legislature Thirty-Third State Legislature
State Capitol, Room 409 State Capitol, Room 431
Honolulu, Hawai'i 96813 Honolulu, Hawai'i 96813
Aloha Senate President Kouchi and Speaker Nakamura:
Arbitration awards (University of Hawai'i and other State Executive Branch
departments) have been issued concerning United Public Workers class action
grievances for Units 1 (Blue Collar Employees) and 10 (Institutional, Health, and
Correctional Workers) relating to temporary hazard pay during the COVID-19 pandemic.
Funding was provided for these awards by Act 29, SLH 2025. However, the
appropriations are insufficient to cover the balance of requirements, so additional
funding is being requested. Additionally, the supplemental award issued for employees
of the other State Executive Branch departments is final.
The following is a summary of the included and excluded requirements of the arbitration
awards for the current fiscal biennium being transmitted to the Legislature for
appropriation. The amounts also reflect funding requirements associated with an
anticipated finalized settlement agreement or arbitration award for the Department of
Education.
FY 26
Salaries and Fringe
General $95,263,742
Interdepartmental Transfers 306,532
Revolving 205,035
Total $95,775,309

The Honorable Ronald D. Kouchi
The Honorable Nadine K. Nakamura
April 23, 2026
Page Two of Two
Attached are proposed drafts Senate Bill No. 3090, S.D. 1, H.D. 2, C.D. 1, and House
Bill No. 2271, H.D. 2, S.D. 1, C.D. 1, which have been updated to reflect the above
noted estimated collective bargaining amounts.
Mahalo,
<2:~
Governor, State of Hawai'i
Attachments
c: Honorable Donovan M. Dela Cruz
Honorable Chris Todd

