HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES 2271
H.B. NO.
THIRTY-THIRD LEGISLATURE, 2026 H.D. 2
STATE OF HAWAII S.D. 1
C.D. 1
PROPOSED
A BILL FOR AN ACT
MAKING EMERGENCY APPROPRIATIONS FOR PUBLIC EMPLOYMENT COST
ITEMS.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 PART I
2 SECTION 1. This Act is recommended by the governor for
3 immediate passage in accordance with section 9 of article VII of
4 the Constitution of the State of Hawaii.
5 PART II
6 SECTION 2. The legislature finds that the appropriation of
7 moneys for collective bargaining cost items associated with
8 labor grievances is necessary to support the fair and timely
9 resolution of employment disputes, maintain labor stability, and
10 ensure the continued effective operation of government services.
11 The legislature further finds that funding of these cost items
12 is in the public interest and necessary to carry out the State's
13 obligations under applicable collective bargaining agreements.
14 In addition, the legislature finds that the State may be
15 subject to potential liabilities arising from labor grievances
16 and that, in certain circumstances, it is prudent to appropriate
17 funds in anticipation of the resolution of such grievances. The
960793 .1

Page 2 2271
H.B. NO.
H.D. 2
S.D. 1
C.D. 1
PROPOSED
1 legislature further finds that such appropriations must not be
2 construed as establishing liability, resolving disputes, or
3 infringing upon the authority of the executive branch to
4 negotiate, settle, or otherwise resolve labor grievances.
5 Further, the legislature finds that the university of
6 Hawaii and certain departments, have used their existing fiscal
7 year 2025-2026 budget to pay collective bargaining cost items
8 related to temporary hazard pay in fiscal year 2025-2026. This
9 action caused a reduction in funds available for departmental
10 operations for the balance of fiscal year 2025-2026.
11 To address the anticipated departmental funding shortfalls
12 due to the temporary hazard pay payouts, a short-term general
13 fund loan will be deposited into a department of budget and
14 finance trust account. The departments shall reclassify the
15 collective bargaining cost items related to temporary hazard pay
16 expenditures from their fiscal year 2025-2026 operating general
17 fund appropriations to the trust account, thereby freeing the
18 appropriations in those operating budget accounts. Upon
19 enactment of this Act and the transfer of appropriated funds to
20 the departments, the departments shall reverse the
21 reclassifications so that the expenditures are restored to their
960793.3

Page 3 H.B. NO. 2271
H.D. 2
S.D. 1
C.D. 1
PROPOSED
1 original operating budget accounts, making the trust account
2 whole.
3 Accordingly, the purposes of this Act are to:
4 (1) Appropriate funds for labor grievances in a manner
5 that is expressly contingent upon the existence of a
6 legally binding obligation, such as an arbitration
7 award or order, court order, or executed settlement
8 agreement, while preserving executive authority,
9 ensuring compliance with applicable laws, and
10 maintaining appropriate fiscal controls; and
11 (2) Authorize the use of the general fund appropriations
12 made in this Act to restore the temporary
13 reclassifications for temporary hazard pay payouts to
14 the appropriate departments to provide for the
15 repayment of the general fund loan.
16 PART III
17 SECTION 3. There are appropriated or authorized from the
18 sources of funding indicated below to collective bargaining
19 statewide (BUF 102) the following sums or so much thereof as may
20 be necessary for fiscal year 2025-2026 to fund collective
21 bargaining cost items associated with grievances filed under
22 agreements negotiated with the exclusive representative of
960793.3

Page 4 H.B. NO. 2271
H.D. 2
S.D. 1
C.D. 1
PROPOSED
1 collective bargaining units (1) and (10), and for their excluded
