1 PART V
2 SECTION 7. Part VI of Act 29, Session Laws of Hawaii 2025,
3 is amended by amending section 11 to read as follows:
4 "SECTION 11. Funds appropriated or authorized by this Act
5 that are not expended or encumbered by June 30, 2026, shall not
6 lapse as of that date[7]; provided that any such unexpended or
7 unencumbered funds shall remain available for expenditure until
8 June 30, 2027."
9 PART VI
SECTION 8. Salary increases and cost adjustments provided
11 in this Act for any officer or employee whose compensation is
12 paid, in whole or in part, from federal, special, or other funds
13 shall be paid wholly or proportionately, as the case may be,
14 from the respective funds; provided that if the respective funds
15 are unable to support such payments, appropriations from other
16 means of financing may be used with the approval of the
17 governor.
SECTION 9. Notwithstanding any provision of this Act, with
19 the approval of the governor, the director of finance may
20 transfer unrequired balances from the appropriated funds as may
21 be available between sections 3 and 4 of this Act as necessary.
